    "Figure 22 presents the distribution of the number of channels used if they are explicitly reported in the reviewed studies.",
    "When the distribution was examined, it is seen that generally 16 (N = 33, 15%) and 32 (N = 19, 9%) channel-devices are more preferred.",
    "It is also observed that 64 (N = 11, 5%) channel-devices are used in a small number of studies.",
    "It is seen that in 7 (3%) of the studies, single-channel devices are used.",
    "In addition, it has been observed that fewer studies use 21 (N = 5, 2%), 62 (N = 4, 2%), 24 (N = 4, 2%), and 19 (N = 3, 2%) channel devices."
